</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="637C3B957A6CFDF8B53516728FBBEEA1" pageId="148" pageNumber="149" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E540449F850895BD7B4142D8519D893D" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="367B4E27965FD59D56159D229C812A50" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">North Portugal and South Spain.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="561402B8314FB01A67DE87C7E32968AD" pageId="148" pageNumber="149" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="199A2F0AD3F5C13613C04521CDA4D3B3" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="90A254A28598AD4035D7148C03FBD1B0" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">Host plant and early stages are unknown. The adults have been collected in the last third of September at altitudes between 560 and 1350 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="43B16D98F45B1F17A34501183D222632" pageId="148" pageNumber="149" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="37A272889BAD06C0FB3612EC2B2AE134" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE9373A1AC7CF96A11F5D4451DBDB82F" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">This species is named after its place of occurrence: the Iberian Peninsula, including Portugal and Spain. The name is a masculine adjective.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
